<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Fractal Manifold"
  description="How Fractal Manifold S.L. collects, uses, and protects personal data under GDPR and LOPDGDD."
  heading="Privacy Policy"
  lang="en"
  alternateHref="/politica-privacidad"
  alternateLabel="Español"
  lastUpdated="April 19, 2026"
>
  <article class="legal-section">
    <h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
    <p>The controller of personal data collected through this website is:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Company:</strong> Fractal Manifold S.L.</li>
      <li><strong>Tax ID (CIF):</strong> B24958753</li>
      <li><strong>Registered Office:</strong> Calle Luis Carrillo de Toledo, 3, 28320 Pinto, Madrid, Spain.</li>
      <li><strong>Contact Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:contact@fractalmanifold.com">contact@fractalmanifold.com</a></li>
    </ul>
  </article>

  <article class="legal-section">
    <h2>2. Personal Data We Collect</h2>
    <p>This website is primarily informational and does not actively collect personal data beyond what you voluntarily provide. Specifically:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Email contact:</strong> when you write to <a href="mailto:contact@fractalmanifold.com">contact@fractalmanifold.com</a>, we receive your email address and any information you include in the message.</li>
      <li><strong>Server logs:</strong> our hosting provider may temporarily record technical data (IP address, user agent, requested URL, timestamp) for security and operational purposes.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not collect browsing data through analytics scripts, advertising trackers, or third-party pixels.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="legal-section">
    <h2>3. Purposes and Legal Basis</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>To respond to your enquiries:</strong> legal basis is your consent (Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR), implied by sending us an email.</li>
      <li><strong>To operate and secure the website:</strong> legal basis is our legitimate interest (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR) in keeping the service online and protected against abuse.</li>
      <li><strong>To comply with legal obligations:</strong> where applicable (Art. 6(1)(c) GDPR).</li>
    </ul>
  </article>

  <article class="legal-section">
    <h2>4. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>Email correspondence is kept only for as long as necessary to handle your enquiry and, where relevant, any subsequent business relationship. Server logs are retained by our hosting provider according to their standard retention periods.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="legal-section">
    <h2>5. Recipients and International Transfers</h2>
    <p>We do not sell or share your personal data with third parties for commercial purposes. The following service providers (processors) may have technical access to the data required to deliver the service:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Hosting:</strong> GitHub Pages (GitHub, Inc., United States). Data transfers to the US are covered by GitHub's Data Processing Addendum and the EU-US Data Privacy Framework.</li>
      <li><strong>Email:</strong> Google Workspace (Google Ireland Limited, Ireland, as main controller for EU users; with international sub-processing by Google LLC in the United States covered by Google's Data Processing Addendum and the EU-US Data Privacy Framework).</li>
    </ul>
  </article>

  <article class="legal-section">
    <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>Under the GDPR and LOPDGDD, you have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Access the personal data we hold about you.</li>
      <li>Request correction of inaccurate data.</li>
      <li>Request erasure ("right to be forgotten") when applicable.</li>
      <li>Restrict or object to the processing of your data.</li>
      <li>Request data portability in a structured, commonly used format.</li>
      <li>Withdraw consent at any time where consent is the legal basis.</li>
      <li>Lodge a complaint with the Spanish Data Protection Agency (AEPD, <a href="https://www.aepd.es" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.aepd.es</a>) if you believe your rights have been infringed.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:contact@fractalmanifold.com">contact@fractalmanifold.com</a>.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="legal-section">
    <h2>7. Cookies</h2>
    <p>This website does not set its own cookies for analytics, advertising, or user profiling. Fonts and static assets are self-hosted and do not issue cookies on our behalf. If a third-party component ever sets a technical cookie strictly necessary for the site to function, it will be limited to that purpose and will not require consent under current Spanish guidance (Guía de Cookies AEPD 2023).</p>
  </article>

  <article class="legal-section">
    <h2>8. Security</h2>
    <p>We apply reasonable technical and organisational measures to protect personal data against unauthorised access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. No method of transmission over the Internet is fully secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="legal-section">
    <h2>9. Changes to this Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes will be reflected in the "Last updated" date below. We recommend checking this page periodically.</p>
  </article>
</LegalLayout>
